<headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 15 at 9:41AM EDT until August 16 at 8:00AM EDT by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM EDT THIS
AFTERNOON THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING...
* WHAT...High risk of rip currents expected.
* WHERE...Ottawa, Erie and Lorain Counties.
* WHEN...From 2 PM EDT this afternoon through Tuesday morning.
* IMPACTS...Wind and wave action will cause currents on the
lakeshore. Swimmers should not enter the water. Currents can
carry swimmers away from shore through a sand bar and along
structures extending out into the lake.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The largest waves and greatest rip
current risk are expected this evening through tonight.</description>
<instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.</instruction>
